cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.GT 

This paper deals with the problem of circuit switch scheduling in large scale data centers, which is a networking problem. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AL (Algorithms) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of linear programming relaxation and randomized rounding techniques further supports the inclusion of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the problem involves scheduling and resource allocation, which could also make it relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
